


  PaRTiKle is an RTOS which provides both, the kernel and the
supporting libraries. The kernel is licensed under the GPL v2 (GNU
GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE) with a explicit declaration of what is
considered "derived work" (see below); and the libraries are licensed
under the LGPL v2.1 (GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE). The files
docs/GPL-2 and docs/LGPL-2.1 contain the full licenses.


For code locate in  the "core" folder:
  These code is released under the GPL-2 license with the following note:
  The license does *not* cover user programs that use kernel services
by normal system calls - this is merely considered normal use of the
kernel, and does *not* fall under the heading of "derived work".  Also
note that the GPL below is copyrighted by the Free Software
Foundation, but the instance of code that it refers to (the PaRTiKle
kernel) is copyrighted by:


For code located in "user" folder:
  This code is released under the LGPL-2.1 license.

